body: Hi you could try to replace `tf.nn.swish` with `x * sigmoid(x)` (its the same). Just fork repo and modify swish function in model.py.

I got the same problem ... its weird, it trained on GCP fine but on uploading to AWS for inference it gave this error, even when I set the TF version to the one I've been using

**ValueError: Unknown activation function:swish**
@shaunster0 Did you tried as @qubvel pointed, replace swish to x * sigmoid(x)

@cruigo93 its too late now I've already done training, i guess i'll have to re-train doing as he says.
Did it work for u?

This is very annoying, please change the base repo to reflect the suggested change. 

Or do another work-around suggestion? Re-training is not always an option.
You dont need to retrain, just change swish and load previous weights.
thanks Pavel, and thanks for ur projects, they’re fantastic!
